00:18:37.450 --> 00:18:42.779
The simplest and easiest way to introduce
natural sunlight into that space would probably

00:18:42.779 --> 00:18:45.419
be to just cut a bunch of holes in the ceiling.

00:18:45.419 --> 00:18:47.940
But unfortunately, the ceiling is Delancey
Street.

00:18:47.940 --> 00:18:50.669
So, that would be, probably, a bad idea, right?

00:18:50.669 --> 00:18:52.610
So, we looked at this.

00:18:52.610 --> 00:18:58.600
Well, actually, it just happened rather, that
I was working on a technology at the time

00:18:58.600 --> 00:19:01.450
that we actually found out about this space.

00:19:01.450 --> 00:19:08.649
And that technology is something that perhaps
we can look to to actually satisfy those needs

00:19:08.649 --> 00:19:12.989
of the space to create an appealing environment
to be used as a public amenity.

00:19:12.989 --> 00:19:16.350
So, what is this technology then?

00:19:16.350 --> 00:19:20.989
Well, this is a very diagrammatic version
of what this tech could be.

00:19:20.989 --> 00:19:26.669
But in a nutshell, at the top side above the
street, like at a lamp post level or something,

00:19:26.669 --> 00:19:32.539
you actually use a system of optics to concentrate
sunlight down into a tiny, tiny footprint,

00:19:32.539 --> 00:19:35.700
a tiny little pellet of super-concentrated
light.

00:19:35.700 --> 00:19:40.470
You take that light, you funnel it through
a tube or a fiber optic cable for that matter.

00:19:40.470 --> 00:19:42.419
And you lead it to where you need it to go.

00:19:42.419 --> 00:19:45.840
And then, you distribute it in the inverse
of the way you gathered it.

00:19:45.840 --> 00:19:51.779
So, in effect, what you've done having gone
through that process is you've created a skylight

00:19:51.779 --> 00:19:55.789
where you couldn't otherwise normally have
a skylight.

00:19:55.789 --> 00:20:01.109
It's very similar, functionally speaking,
it's a fairly straightforward idea.

00:20:01.109 --> 00:20:05.480
Functionally speaking, it's very similar to
a periscope or even an endoscope--something

00:20:05.480 --> 00:20:06.870
like that.

00:20:06.870 --> 00:20:10.879
But it's really just an optical device that
allows us to do this, right?

00:20:10.879 --> 00:20:15.989
So, that has some pretty obvious advantages
for this specific site in that you've distilled

00:20:15.989 --> 00:20:21.470
the footprint of the sky and sunlight down
to a tiny little point and that's all you're

00:20:21.470 --> 00:20:22.470
cutting in the street.

00:20:22.470 --> 00:20:27.539
So, you can free up the street level for cars
and people and dogs or whatever, and actually

00:20:27.539 --> 00:20:32.280
just run this thing down there and then redistribute
it and then spread it back out and actually

00:20:32.280 --> 00:20:38.799
achieve an effect where what you're looking
up at down in the space is a simulacrum of

00:20:38.799 --> 00:20:42.009
what you're looking at with the collectors
above.

00:20:42.009 --> 00:20:48.380
So, that's all fine and well, conceptually,
but we felt like we needed to actually see

00:20:48.380 --> 00:20:50.590
if this idea--this kooky idea--worked.

00:20:50.590 --> 00:20:58.049
So, we gathered together a few friends and
we went through the process of actually engineering

00:20:58.049 --> 00:21:04.639
a system like this, and designing it and actually
fabricating it, too, which was a very telling

00:21:04.639 --> 00:21:05.710
process.

00:21:05.710 --> 00:21:12.389
In the end--this was probably last summer--we
ended up in the fifth floor walk-up of a buddy

00:21:12.389 --> 00:21:18.109
of mine, sweating in the middle of summertime
in Chinatown, screwing together this device.

00:21:18.109 --> 00:21:21.159
But so, it's very homemade.

00:21:21.159 --> 00:21:28.090
But at the same time, we realized that it
is something that is possible and it is doable

00:21:28.090 --> 00:21:29.519
and it works.

00:21:29.519 --> 00:21:31.710
It's actually a fairly old process.

00:21:31.710 --> 00:21:35.840
I mean, hearkening back to ancient Egypt,
they would cut shafts through their ceilings

00:21:35.840 --> 00:21:39.440
to reflect light down into the tombs and stuff.

00:21:39.440 --> 00:21:41.509
The skylight is obviously a version.

00:21:41.509 --> 00:21:45.700
There's an invention called the "solar tube,"
that also accomplishes something very similar.

00:21:45.700 --> 00:21:49.799
So, really this is just a variation on a very
ancient theme.

00:21:49.799 --> 00:21:50.799
All right?

00:21:50.799 --> 00:21:51.799
So, we built one.

