00:50:29.250 --> 00:50:31.430
We haven't really specified what goes on in
there.

00:50:31.430 --> 00:50:33.590
We're deliberately leaving these things blank.

00:50:33.590 --> 00:50:36.509
We haven't specified what these things above
ground actually look like.

00:50:36.509 --> 00:50:40.010
We haven't specified what the entries look
like.

00:50:40.010 --> 00:50:44.160
And so, I mean, I think all of those things
are open and probably would be benefited by

00:50:44.160 --> 00:50:47.079
some sort of competition.

00:50:47.079 --> 00:50:53.770
What we're proposing is actually in and of
itself already so specific that it would be

00:50:53.770 --> 00:51:02.759
hard for me to envision the, I guess, within
this defined set of design constraints, all

00:51:02.759 --> 00:51:04.990
this diversity of ideas that the High Line
generated.

00:51:04.990 --> 00:51:08.769
Like, you will recall, there was one that
turned the entire thing into a pool.

00:51:08.769 --> 00:51:12.059
There's one that turned the entire thing into
a jail.

00:51:12.059 --> 00:51:19.131
I think that we could, well, we could turn
this whole thing into a pool, certainly, or

00:51:19.131 --> 00:51:21.180
an ice rink, or a jail.

00:51:21.180 --> 00:51:22.190
Actually, it would make a really good jail.

00:51:22.190 --> 00:51:24.369
&gt;&gt;Dan Barasch: A really fun jail.

00:51:24.369 --> 00:51:26.819
[laughter]
&gt;&gt;James Ramsey: But in and of--.

00:51:26.819 --> 00:51:31.359
The design is actually, again, the concept
itself is so specific already.

00:51:31.359 --> 00:51:33.140
It makes it a little bit challenging to do
that.

00:51:33.140 --> 00:51:36.260
&gt;&gt;Dan Barasch: But actually just on that point,
I mean, I think there's three classes at Columbia

00:51:36.260 --> 00:51:41.690
University that are like, teaching or they
are using this as architecture studios.

00:51:41.690 --> 00:51:46.559
And we get a lot of people reaching out to
us from NYU, from a lot of other universities,

00:51:46.559 --> 00:51:47.559
literally around the world.

00:51:47.559 --> 00:51:51.660
So, I think there already have been or are
going to be a lot of really amazing ideas

00:51:51.660 --> 00:51:52.880
that come out of this.

00:51:52.880 --> 00:51:58.440
And I think it'll be fun to bring people in
to the idea over the next year.

