00:52:49.670 --> 00:52:51.019
It's really good.

00:52:51.019 --> 00:52:57.109
Anyway, so first of all, the site immediately
to the south was knocked down in the Robert

00:52:57.109 --> 00:52:59.160
Moses era.

00:52:59.160 --> 00:53:04.609
It looked a lot like the neighborhood to the
north and it was just unceremoniously bulldozed

00:53:04.609 --> 00:53:09.680
to make way for, I don't know, either for
progress or to get rid of dirtiness.

00:53:09.680 --> 00:53:11.369
It's unclear which of the two it was.

00:53:11.369 --> 00:53:16.809
But they actually never built back what they
had originally planned for that neighborhood

00:53:16.809 --> 00:53:18.380
right there.

00:53:18.380 --> 00:53:28.030
And because this neighborhood happens really
at the nexus point of so many different ethnicities

00:53:28.030 --> 00:53:31.339
and neighborhoods, I mean, you've got the
Orthodox Jewish community, you've got the

00:53:31.339 --> 00:53:35.480
Chinese, you've got the Dominicans, you've
got the Puerto Ricans, you've got the hipsters,

00:53:35.480 --> 00:53:39.279
all meeting at this one little point, it's
been a hotly contested neighborhood for something

00:53:39.279 --> 00:53:40.279
like 40 years.

00:53:40.279 --> 00:53:46.279
And as a result, they have not reached a consensus
to build something there until very recently

00:53:46.279 --> 00:53:47.279
anyway.

00:53:47.279 --> 00:53:48.769
So, within the last what?

00:53:48.769 --> 00:53:52.499
Year, year and a half, something like that,
they finally reached a consensus for what

00:53:52.499 --> 00:53:54.000
to do with it.

00:53:54.000 --> 00:53:59.220
And this is the part that relates directly
to what you're talking about demographically.

00:53:59.220 --> 00:54:03.509
The consensus that they reached is they're
gonna build a million and a half square feet

00:54:03.509 --> 00:54:06.640
distributed across all of these sites.

00:54:06.640 --> 00:54:12.990
And almost half of that square footage is
going to be devoted specifically to affordable

00:54:12.990 --> 00:54:13.990
housing.

00:54:13.990 --> 00:54:22.430
So, I think we have a built-in system for
that development itself that actually very

00:54:22.430 --> 00:54:26.690
strongly preserves the demographic mix of
the neighborhood.

00:54:26.690 --> 00:54:28.680
&gt;&gt;Dan Barasch: Cool.

